From 8e09460bb5675984ad5b12c46cf6e418fda243e8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Mon, 19 Jan 2026 19:01:04 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] Add multiplayer support with WebSocket server for Risk
 game

- Create Node.js WebSocket server for coordinating multiplayer games
- Add client-side network module for WebSocket communication
- Add human players slider to select number of human players
- Implement game lobby system with create/join functionality
- Add waiting room screen for players to join before game starts
- Broadcast game actions (claim, place, attack, fortify) to all players
- Synchronize game state across all connected clients
- Add player join/leave announcements
- Preserve offline single-player mode (1 human + AI works without server)
- Add lobby-specific voice and AI delay settings
- Update CSS with lobby and games list styling

Multiplayer mode is enabled when human players > 1. The server can be
started with 'npm start' in the Risk directory.
---
